    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method is called when your app creates or restores an instance of your user interface."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When the user or your app requests a new instance of your user interface, UIKit creates an appropriate scene object and connects it to your app. Use this method to respond to the addition of the new scene and to begin loading any data that the scene needs to display. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When your app responds to scene activations requests, for example, by using "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiapplication/3197901-requestscenesessionactivation"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the user activity is in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisceneconnectionoptions/3238074-useractivities"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " set provided by options. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When the user reactivates an instance of your user interface, UIKit creates a scene object and populates it with saved state, provided by  "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiscenedelegate/3238061-staterestorationactivityforscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". When your app restores state, the user activity is presented in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiscenesession/3197959-staterestorationactivity"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of session."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In addition to calling this method, UIKit also posts a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiscenewillconnectnotification"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " notification.  "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
